cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the application of linear network coding to wireless broadcasting with feedback, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the sparsity of encoding vectors, which is a topic in sparse signal processing (cs.SI). The algorithm developed in the paper involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and the simulations conducted in the paper involve data structures (cs.DS).
